PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778976177
OL,3,CUK gives eccentric Eurovision
OL,4,Cperformance as Israel draws protest
OL,6,FInside the arena, the show appeared to
OL,7,Fmostly run without a hitch, with the
OL,8,Fnight opening with a performance from
OL,9,Flast year's winner JJ, before
OL,10,FDenmark's Soren Torpegaard Lund became
OL,11,Fthe first act to compete.
OL,13,FIsrael's Noam Bettan's performed
OL,14,Fthird, with some chants and booing
OL,15,Fheard in the crowd but many Israeli
OL,16,Fflags and banners also seen.
OL,18,FThe 28-year-old, who sang his song
OL,19,FMichelle, in English, Hebrew and
OL,20,FFrench, had been booed during his
OL,21,Fperformance at Tuesday's semi-final.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778976177
OL,3,CUK gives eccentric Eurovision
OL,4,Cperformance as Israel draws protest
OL,6,FFurther into the show, Australian pop
OL,7,Fstar Delta Goodrem performed her song
OL,8,FEclipse, accompanied by a harpist,
OL,9,Fbefore eventually playing a gold
OL,10,Fsparkly piano herself.
OL,12,FThe former Neighbours star is a
OL,13,Ffavourite of the competition, and
OL,14,Fended her song by being elevated into
OL,15,Fthe air from the top of the piano, as
OL,16,Ffireworks went off around her.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
